<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,814,1236]" box="[151,1194,814,840]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[151,235,814,840]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female</emphasis>
. Posterior margin of seventh sternite with prominent convex median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1181,814,840]" captionStart="FIGURES 10" captionStartId="45.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1374,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[197,1391,166,1888]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 10 A–L. Female sternite VII of Coelidiini. A. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.; B. C. ostenta (Distant); C. C. kodikanelensis Nielson; D. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao). E. Olidiana brevis (Walker); F. O. kirkaldyi (Nielson); G. O. umroensis sp. nov.; H. Singillatus serratispatulatus sp. nov.; I. Trinoridia dialata sp. nov.; J. T. piperica sp. nov.; K. T. ramamurthyi sp. nov.; L. Webbolidia andamana sp. nov.; L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366564/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10 F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,814,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[199,397,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Valvula I with sculptured area restricted to apical ¼ (
<figureCitation box="[993,1071,850,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[196,1298,203,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 12 A–P. Female valvula I and II. Olidiana brevis (Walker): A &amp; B. Valvula I; C &amp; D. Valvula II. O. kirkaldyi (Nielson): E&amp; F. Valvula I; G &amp; H. Valvula II. O. umroensis sp. nov.: I &amp; J. Valvula I; K &amp; L. Valvula II. Singillatus serratispatulatus sp. nov.: M &amp; N. Valvula I; O &amp; P. Valvula II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366568/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs12</figureCitation>
E–F). Valvula II with prominent teeth widely separated from each other, toothed area confined to apical 1/3 (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1093,886,912]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[196,1298,203,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 12 A–P. Female valvula I and II. Olidiana brevis (Walker): A &amp; B. Valvula I; C &amp; D. Valvula II. O. kirkaldyi (Nielson): E&amp; F. Valvula I; G &amp; H. Valvula II. O. umroensis sp. nov.: I &amp; J. Valvula I; K &amp; L. Valvula II. Singillatus serratispatulatus sp. nov.: M &amp; N. Valvula I; O &amp; P. Valvula II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366568/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 12</figureCitation>
G–H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,814,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[199,369,923,948]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Measurements.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[375,433,922,948]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Male</collectingRegion>
<quantity box="[439,575,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.449999999999999" metricValueMax="6.6" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="6.449999999999999" valueMax="6.6" valueMin="6.3">6.3−6.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[645,730,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 2.0 mm wide across posterolateral angels of pronotum. Female 
<quantity box="[395,532,958,984]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="7.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="7.55" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="7.3">7.3−7.8 mm</quantity>
long, 2.0 mm wide across eyes and 
<quantity box="[941,1028,958,984]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,814,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[199,424,1030,1056]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Material Examined.</emphasis>
Several males and females from, 
<collectingCountry box="[807,891,1030,1056]" name="India" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">INDIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[901,1081,1030,1056]" country="India" name="Andhra Pradesh" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Andhra Pradesh</collectingRegion>
(Varni), 
<collectingRegion box="[1182,1297,1030,1056]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
(Bangalore, Bidar, Chikkaballapura, Kollegal, Melkote, Mudigree, Nandi Hills, Punjanur forest, Sirsi, Vijayapura), 
<collectingRegion box="[1300,1375,1066,1092]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Kerala</collectingRegion>
(Walayar), 
<collectingRegion box="[233,357,1102,1128]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
(Shillong), 
<collectingRegion box="[496,606,1102,1128]" country="India" name="Rajasthan" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Rajasthan</collectingRegion>
(Udaipur), 
<collectingRegion box="[741,876,1102,1128]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
(Srivilliputtur, Kallar, Kodaikanal), 
<collectingRegion box="[1293,1436,1102,1128]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
(Kolkata).The specimens were collected during April, to September. It breeds on 
<taxonomicName authority="Lam." authorityName="Lam." box="[1070,1364,1138,1164]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Ziziphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis box="[1070,1297,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ziziphus mauritiana</emphasis>
Lam.
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 54" captionStartId="89.[151,264,1770,1795]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,186,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@89.[190,1397,181,1745]" captionTargetPageId="89" captionText="FIGURES 54 A–E. Coelidiini in their natural habitat.A&amp;B. Trinoridia dialata sp. nov. early stage nymph (A) and adult attend- ed by ant, Campnotus sp. on Morinda tinctoria; C&amp;D. Olidiana kirkaldyi (Nielson) nymph and adult on Ziziphus mauritiana leaf; E. Olidiana brevis (Walker); F. Olidiana umroensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366652/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 54</figureCitation>
C–D) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[303,573,1174,1200]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Dodonaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viscosa">
<emphasis box="[303,508,1174,1200]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Dodonaea viscosa</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1144,1210,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,814,1236]" box="[199,1144,1210,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1210,1236]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the most common coelidiine species found in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[1022,1141,1210,1236]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
